# .ultra.md — Apple Ultra Project Context
*Example for Acme Scheduling (fictional). Copy and customize via ultra-teach.*

## Product
Acme Scheduling lets local businesses accept online bookings with payments and reminders.
Stage: growth
Primary action: book an appointment
Type: scheduling/booking
Register: Product

## Users
Primary user: small business owner (salon, clinic, tutor) — low technical sophistication
Job-to-be-done: fill calendar without phone tag and no-shows
Failure mode: double-booking, missed payment, customer shows up at wrong time

## Design
Creative North Star: The Reception Desk — calm, clear, never flashy on the booking path
System: shadcn/ui + Tailwind tokens in globals.css
Key tokens: cobalt primary, violet accent, amber pending, emerald confirmed; Cal Sans display

Named Rules:
- **The One Accent Rule.** Only cobalt is saturated on booking surfaces — status colors are semantic only.
- **The Flat Booking Card Rule.** Booking hub cards use fill hierarchy, not glass or heavy shadow.
- **The No-Pink-on-Booking Rule.** Rose/pink reserved for marketing — never on /book flows.

## Benchmarks
Positive: Linear, Stripe Checkout, Cal.com
Anti: generic AI SaaS dashboards, purple gradient KPI heroes
Priority dimension: seamlessness

## Stack
Verify: npm run verify
Migrations: drizzle/
Schema: src/db/schema.ts
API patterns: cron Bearer, dashboard session, v1 API keys

## Known Issues
- Settings page density on mobile
Off-limits: legacy embed widget CSS (deprecating Q3)

